BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2026-07-22-emergent-sparsity-frozen-random-cnn@dlrtp
DTSTAMP:20260720T122128Z
DTSTART:20260722T160000Z
DTEND:20260722T180000Z
SUMMARY:DLRTP Weekly — Emergent Sparsity in Frozen-Random-CNN Deep RL (Sc
 ott Norton)
LOCATION:Frontier RTP\, 800 Park Offices Dr\, Durham\, NC
DESCRIPTION:Playing Pong through 3 neurons: freeze a randomly initialized C
 NN\, train a deep RL agent on top\, and the agent spontaneously compresses
  all task-relevant information through as few as 1-3 of the 64 neurons in 
 its first fully-connected layer\, with no sparsity objective anywhere. Sco
 tt Norton presents his manuscript (arXiv pending) documenting the phenomen
 on in Atari Pong. No RL background required\; the setting is informal and 
 open to everyone. Find us in the Eagles room off the main coworking area.\
 nRSVP: https://www.meetup.com/deep-learning-rtp/events/315516897/
URL:https://www.meetup.com/deep-learning-rtp/events/315516897/
END:VEVENT
